-- Massachusetts Police Say Second Suspect in Custody
-- B y
-- 2013-04-20T03:36:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-20/massachusetts-police-say-second-suspect-in-custody-video-.html
Massachusetts  Governor Deval 
Patrick, State Police Colonel Timothy Alben, U.S. Attorney 
Carmen Ortiz, Boston Mayor Tom Menino, Richard DesLauriers, 
special agent in charge of the Boston FBI office, Boston Police 
Commissioner Ed Davis, Watertown Police Chief Edward Deveau and 
Massachusetts Bay Transportation Authority Police Chief Paul 
MacMillan, about speak at a news conference in Watertown, 
Massachusetts about the capture of the second suspect in the 
Boston Marathon bombing.   Dzhokar Tsarnaev, 19, was apprehended at house in 
Watertown where he was hiding after an almost 24-hour manhunt 
that shut down  Boston and surrounding cities. (Source: 
Bloomberg)  Running Time: 21:54
 